my criminology professor.

4
00:00:06,087 --> 00:00:07,252
Are you gonna tell him?

5
00:00:07,253 --> 00:00:09,304
You know the rules, honey. I have to.

6
00:00:12,190 --> 00:00:15,449
Shrink asked if a lifetime without
a libido was such a bad thing.

7
00:00:15,450 --> 00:00:16,955
I think she's given up on me.

8
00:00:16,956 --> 00:00:18,141
You just need more time.

9
00:00:18,142 --> 00:00:21,469
And I think we can take a tough
but survivable amount of pain now...

10
00:00:21,470 --> 00:00:24,797
Or stay together and deal
with unbearable pain later.

11
00:00:24,798 --> 00:00:26,552
So, I vote for the pain now.

12
00:00:32,424 --> 00:00:34,329
You should hire
someone to do this.

13
00:00:34,751 --> 00:00:36,522
Hey, you're lucky I'm not a farmer.

14
00:00:36,523 --> 00:00:38,385
You'd be out ploughing a field.

15
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:40,436
What is manila anyway?

16
00:00:40,437 --> 00:00:41,437
I don't know.

17
00:00:42,096 --> 00:00:44,676
Is it a substance, a colour maybe?

18
00:00:44,677 --> 00:00:47,016
"In the kitchen,
we'll do a nice manila."

19
00:00:47,337 --> 00:00:50,580
I'd say more like,
"by the time we dug him up,

20
00:00:50,581 --> 00:00:52,065
he turned manila."

21
00:00:52,449 --> 00:00:54,564
Don't you have to get to class?

22
00:00:54,565 --> 00:00:55,855
On my way.

23
00:00:56,198 --> 00:00:59,723
Oh, and Wikipedia says:
"Not a what, but a where,

24
00:00:59,724 --> 00:01:02,772
called 'manila' after hemp
from the Philippines."

25
00:01:05,064 --> 00:01:06,042
Oh.

26
00:01:06,109 --> 00:01:07,268
Good Morning.

27
00:01:07,269 --> 00:01:10,971
Guess that would explain why
this filing was giving me a killer buzz.

28
00:01:11,827 --> 00:01:13,329
Oh.

29
00:01:14,131 --> 00:01:16,183
Can I help you, Mrs. O'Dell?

30
00:01:16,184 --> 00:01:18,137
I hope so, Mr. Mars.

31
00:01:18,666 --> 00:01:19,865
Please, come in.

32
00:01:26,998 --> 00:01:28,860
My husband didn't kill himself.

33
00:01:29,503 --> 00:01:30,950
What makes you think that?

34
00:01:31,138 --> 00:01:33,178
Because I know my husband.

35
00:01:33,179 --> 00:01:35,290
Mrs. O'Dell, I saw him that night.

36
00:01:35,291 --> 00:01:38,397
He had just learned of your infidelity.
He was drinking heavily.

37
00:01:38,398 --> 00:01:40,431
Well, it was in him to sulk,

38
00:01:40,432 --> 00:01:42,274
to divorce me, even, but...

39
00:01:42,275 --> 00:01:45,707
he would never in a million
years kill himself over me.

40
00:01:45,708 --> 00:01:47,804
The sheriff ruled it a
suicide six weeks ago.

41
00:01:47,805 --> 00:01:48,805
Why come to me now?

42
00:01:48,806 --> 00:01:51,025
Honestly? Money.

43
00:01:51,326 --> 00:01:53,524
As his death was ruled a suicide,

44
00:01:53,559 --> 00:01:56,384
his life insurance is denying benefits.

45
00:01:56,385 --> 00:01:58,800
I'm a widow with two
children to take care of.

46
00:01:58,801 --> 00:02:02,791
You told Mr. O'Dell you were at a junior
league meeting the night he died.

47
00:02:02,792 --> 00:02:04,624
Are you asking for my alibi?

48
00:02:04,625 --> 00:02:07,292
If it is a murder, you'll be
asked for it repeatedly.

49
00:02:07,293 --> 00:02:08,988
Your husband implied that...

50
00:02:08,989 --> 00:02:12,337
