62
00:02:47,933 --> 00:02:49,057
I did.

63
00:02:49,958 --> 00:02:51,481
We had a break-in.

64
00:02:51,482 --> 00:02:54,410
Our computer was sabotaged,
and it's dead.

65
00:02:54,411 --> 00:02:57,658
There's a year's worth of
research on that hard drive.

66
00:02:57,659 --> 00:03:01,432
Our professor will have med
students practicing autopsies on us.

67
00:03:01,433 --> 00:03:04,412
Professor McGregor has to
understand it's not our fault.

68
00:03:05,488 --> 00:03:07,682
I locked up, Pauline.

69
00:03:07,683 --> 00:03:09,260
Do you have a backup?

70
00:03:09,261 --> 00:03:11,097
Yeah. He's gone, too.

71
00:03:11,098 --> 00:03:13,303
Your backup's a he?

72
00:03:13,304 --> 00:03:15,741
Twenty-five, our research monkey.

73
00:03:15,742 --> 00:03:18,549
He is the research.

74
00:03:18,550 --> 00:03:21,835
Even if you save the hard drive, without
Twenty-five, the whole project is dead.

75
00:03:21,836 --> 00:03:24,880
And we'll be dead, too,
if McGregor finds out we lost him.

76
00:03:24,881 --> 00:03:29,475
Who do you go to, to find a stolen
monkey and twenty control-group rats?

77
00:03:32,686 --> 00:03:34,914
Logan Echolls, don't you get it?

78
00:03:34,915 --> 00:03:37,928
Ex-boyfriend.
That's your new title.

79
00:03:37,929 --> 00:03:40,125
It comes with certain restrictions.

80
00:03:40,126 --> 00:03:41,918
This is my Food Court time.

81
00:03:41,919 --> 00:03:45,652
You're not a breakfast person.
You're not even an early-lunch kind of guy.

82
00:03:45,653 --> 00:03:48,550
Can't we just agree
this is Veronica time?

83
00:03:48,551 --> 00:03:49,478
- Veronica!
- Mac!

84
00:03:50,262 --> 00:03:52,484
And the people coming
to take me away.

85
00:03:52,485 --> 00:03:56,275
Veronica Mars, Pauline Elliott
and Gil Thomas Pardy.

86
00:03:56,276 --> 00:03:58,317
They're missing a monkey.

87
00:03:58,518 --> 00:04:00,745
And twenty rats.

88
00:04:00,746 --> 00:04:03,398
- We're talking "monkey" as in...
- "Touch my..."

89
00:04:03,399 --> 00:04:05,103
It's not just any monkey.

90
00:04:05,104 --> 00:04:07,039
Please tell me he plays piano.

91
00:04:07,040 --> 00:04:09,643
Twenty-five is a genetically
altered capuchin monkey.

92
00:04:09,644 --> 00:04:11,665
Its uptake-inhibitor proteins
have been coded...

93
00:04:11,666 --> 00:04:14,520
to allow us to monitor cholesterol
breakdown at a cellular level.

94
00:04:16,482 --> 00:04:17,973
And he can play "Chopsticks."

95
00:04:17,974 --> 00:04:19,286
Excellent.

96
00:04:20,906 --> 00:04:23,844
Any idea who would want to nab...

97
00:04:24,145 --> 00:04:26,582
Um, what's his name again?

98
00:04:26,583 --> 00:04:27,711
It's not a pet.

99
00:04:27,712 --> 00:04:31,214
We don't name them or wrap
squeaky toys up for Christmas.

100
00:04:31,215 --> 00:04:33,260
His research ID number is twenty-five.

101
00:04:33,295 --> 00:04:35,183
Yes, I know exactly who stole him.

102
00:04:35,184 --> 00:04:36,721
It was those damn fat kids.

103
00:04:36,722 --> 00:04:38,891
Because, I take it,
monkeys are delicious?

104
00:04:38,892 --> 00:04:40,071
And, dude...

105
00:04:40,072 --> 00:04:42,865
"girth-challenged" is the
preferred nomenclature.

106
00:04:42,866 --> 00:04:46,488
P-H-A-T: People for
Humane Animal Treatment.

107
00:04:46,489 --> 00:04:47,900
They've done this kind of crap before.

108
00:04:47,901 --> 00:04:49,555
They liberated him...

109
00:04:49,556 --> 00:04:52,822
and took a year's worth
of research in the process.

110
00:04:53,123 --> 00:04:55,667
Please, this is our future.

111
00:04:56,827 --> 00:04:58,351
We need that monkey back.

112
00:05:01,438 --> 00:05:03,438
Veronica Mars

113
00:05:03,439 --> 00:05:06,439
3X10 "Show me the monkey"

114
