115
00:05:22,344 --> 00:05:24,344
Vieni a trovarci!

116
00:05:24,345 --> 00:05:28,345
veronicamars.it

117
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:34,313
I just can't wait for that moment
when you're in a tree, going...

118
00:05:34,314 --> 00:05:36,317
"here, monkey, monkey,"
and holding out a banana,

119
00:05:36,318 --> 00:05:39,037
and then the branch breaks
and hilarity ensues.

120
00:05:39,131 --> 00:05:41,362
Ah, if there's hilarity, I charge extra.

121
00:05:41,563 --> 00:05:43,983
Think you can salvage
anything off their hard drive?

122
00:05:43,984 --> 00:05:46,418
Iffy. Looks like someone
poured something on it.

123
00:05:46,419 --> 00:05:47,319
Aha!

124
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:48,497
You've solved the case.

125
00:05:49,483 --> 00:05:52,173
PHAT is having a
recruitment meeting tonight.

126
00:05:52,174 --> 00:05:53,233
Square one.

127
00:05:53,234 --> 00:05:54,986
Want some company?

128
00:05:55,696 --> 00:05:56,749
What?

129
00:05:56,750 --> 00:05:58,267
This soft spot here...

130
00:05:58,268 --> 00:05:59,444
It's for all creatures,
great and small.

131
00:05:59,518 --> 00:06:01,288
Okay, the more, the merrier.

132
00:06:01,289 --> 00:06:04,243
All we need is one more angel,
and we've got a show.

133
00:06:04,244 --> 00:06:06,298
I'll come by your room.
Dress cruelty-free.

134
00:06:06,299 --> 00:06:07,455
We want to blend.

135
00:06:07,456 --> 00:06:09,311
Got it. Off to class.

136
00:06:15,362 --> 00:06:17,140
- Hi!
- Hi.

137
00:06:17,141 --> 00:06:18,938
- What are you doing here?
- Looking for you.

138
00:06:18,939 --> 00:06:20,154
I need to find Weevil.

139
00:06:20,155 --> 00:06:21,683
You two palling around now?

140
00:06:21,684 --> 00:06:23,375
I need to ask him some questions.

141
00:06:23,376 --> 00:06:26,214
Mindy O'Dell doesn't think
her husband killed himself,

142
00:06:26,215 --> 00:06:27,615
and Weevil found the body, so...

143
00:06:27,708 --> 00:06:29,480
You think Dean O'Dell was murdered?

144
00:06:29,481 --> 00:06:30,953
Uh-uh. Not really.

145
00:06:30,954 --> 00:06:34,061
I think he had his heart
broken and shot himself.

146
00:06:34,062 --> 00:06:36,800
I suspect his wife feels a
tremendous amount of guilt.

147
00:06:36,835 --> 00:06:37,888
So why take the case?

148
00:06:37,889 --> 00:06:39,419
I haven't yet. I'm checking it out.

149
00:06:40,171 --> 00:06:42,091
Physical plant after 6:00.

150
00:06:42,381 --> 00:06:45,495
How did you find me?
My cell phone is not on.

151
00:06:45,496 --> 00:06:47,006
Maybe I'll tell you someday.

152
00:06:48,893 --> 00:06:51,356
According to the PHAT website...

153
00:06:51,357 --> 00:06:54,144
we should stay away from fur, obviously,

154
00:06:54,179 --> 00:06:56,519
down, leather...

155
00:06:56,979 --> 00:06:59,078
The one day I feel like
wearing a leather miniskirt.

156
00:06:59,411 --> 00:07:02,562
If it ever had a face or parents,
you can't wear it.

157
00:07:02,563 --> 00:07:04,389
So my mollusc shoes are cool?

158
00:07:04,390 --> 00:07:07,511
Oh, does this say "cruelty-free"?

159
00:07:08,446 --> 00:07:09,270
It says...

160
00:07:09,271 --> 00:07:10,923
"I've given up.

161
00:07:10,924 --> 00:07:12,154
Don't look at me."

162
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:15,246
Hey!

163
00:07:15,682 --> 00:07:17,774
You guys haven't
picked a country yet.

164
00:07:17,775 --> 00:07:19,662
For the around-the-world party.

165
00:07:20,194 --> 00:07:22,958
Every dorm room dresses itself
up like a different country.

166
00:07:22,959 --> 00:07:24,739
Party, fun?

167
00:07:25,823 --> 00:07:26,718
No?

168
00:07:26,719 --> 00:07:29,333
I prefer most of the people on the floor,

169
00:07:29,334 --> 00:07:31,369
you know, not in my room.

170
00:07:31,370 --> 00:07:32,370
Okay.

171
00:07:32,371 --> 00:07:34,474
well, if you change your mind,
let me know soon.

172
00:07:34,475 --> 00:07:36,494
Most of Western Europe goes down fast.

173
00:07:40,377 --> 00:07:41,331
Single.

174
00:07:41,332 --> 00:07:43,585
Single and on the rebound.

175
00:07:43,981 --> 00:07:45,210
Just so you know,

176
00:07:45,211 --> 00:07:47,931
we're approaching critical,
pathetic mass...

177
00:07:47,932 --> 00:07:50,753
if the girl who most wants
to host gentlemen callers...

178
00:07:50,754 --> 00:07:53,535
is the most recent victim
of a sexual assault.

179
00:07:54,675 --> 00:07:56,482
We should be out there!

180
00:07:57,004 --> 00:08:00,304
Or, at the very least, not barring
them from coming to us.

181
00:08:06,011 --> 00:08:06,975
Okay.

182
00:08:06,976 --> 00:08:09,220
I get cruelty-free,
but I'm an animal, too,

183
00:08:09,255 --> 00:08:12,289
and the clove cigarettes and
no-bathing thing is cruelty to me.

184
00:08:13,482 --> 00:08:15,257
Oh. No. Not you.

185
00:08:15,258 --> 00:08:17,181
You're... fine!

186
00:08:17,782 --> 00:08:20,095
You guys ever been to one
of these things before?

187
00:08:20,396 --> 00:08:23,962
Me? No. I come from a
meat-and-potatoes kind of family,

188
00:08:23,963 --> 00:08:25,207
minus the potatoes.

189
00:08:25,208 --> 00:08:26,979
My first pacifier was made of jerky.

190
00:08:28,110 --> 00:08:30,202
Well, it, uh, it could be fun.

191
00:08:30,203 --> 00:08:33,856
Or it could be a lot of speechmaking
by politicos-in-training.

192
00:08:33,857 --> 00:08:36,141
Or that.

193
00:08:38,939 --> 00:08:40,661
My name is Bronson Pope.

194
00:08:40,662 --> 00:08:43,565
I'm the chapter president
of PHAT here at Hearst.

195
00:08:45,139 --> 00:08:48,163
I'd like to thank everyone
for coming out.

196
00:08:50,660 --> 00:08:54,261
From food industries to clothing
to medical research,

197
00:08:54,262 --> 00:08:57,541
corporate America employs
horrible cruelty to animals,

198
00:08:57,542 --> 00:08:59,911
simply to maximize profit.

199
00:08:59,912 --> 00:09:03,921
It's a tragic state of affairs
that we fight with education.

200
00:09:03,922 --> 00:09:06,539
People who disagree aren't the enemy.

201
00:09:06,540 --> 00:09:07,704
They're the goal.

202
00:09:09,732 --> 00:09:10,554
Yeah?

203
00:09:10,622 --> 00:09:14,093
This is in addition to some
of the more active stuff?

204
00:09:14,094 --> 00:09:16,126
There was a rumour that someone...

205
00:09:16,127 --> 00:09:17,758
liberated some research animals.

206
00:09:17,759 --> 00:09:19,836
I was just wondering if...

207
00:09:19,837 --> 00:09:21,917
we'd be doing anything like that.

208
00:09:21,918 --> 00:09:23,906
What? I raised my hand.

209
00:09:23,907 --> 00:09:26,103
That's really not our thing,

210
00:09:26,104 --> 00:09:28,007
but if you're eager for action...

211
00:09:28,008 --> 00:09:30,832
how about joining us tomorrow night
to launch our letter-writing campaign?

212
00:09:30,833 --> 00:09:33,317
Sure. That sounds almost as good.

213
00:09:33,318 --> 00:09:37,086
You know, Bronson, that psycho
bow-hunting rocker guy Ed Argent...

214
00:09:37,087 --> 00:09:39,000
is playing downtown tomorrow night.

215
00:09:39,001 --> 00:09:41,124
We should consider picketing the show.

216
00:09:41,125 --> 00:09:43,065
You ever meet an Argent fan, Darla?

217
00:09:43,066 --> 00:09:45,888
Uh, they'd pay double
to spit on our picket line.

218
00:09:48,862 --> 00:09:50,805
So, I came in at around seven.

219
00:09:50,806 --> 00:09:52,414
First, I thought he just...

220
00:09:52,415 --> 00:09:54,504
had a bender and fell asleep at his desk,

221
00:09:54,505 --> 00:09:57,225
but then I saw blood...
and the note.

222
00:09:57,226 --> 00:09:58,767
A note?

223
00:09:58,768 --> 00:10:00,111
Yeah, on the computer.

224
00:10:00,112 --> 00:10:02,189
He had a memo on the screen, saying...

225
00:10:02,190 --> 00:10:05,598
"Goodbye, cruel world zzzz."

226
00:10:05,599 --> 00:10:08,599
I guess his head fell on the Z.

227
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:10,798
It's a shame, man.

228
00:10:10,799 --> 00:10:12,116
He was pretty cool...

229
00:10:12,314 --> 00:10:14,031
for a weird...

230
00:10:14,032 --> 00:10:15,149
old

231
00:10:15,150 --> 00:10:16,372
white dude.

232
00:10:18,244 --> 00:10:19,913
So, uh, what?

233
00:10:19,914 --> 00:10:22,350
You just wanted to
see if he left any booze?

234
00:10:41,487 --> 00:10:44,676
I think I told you, the management
asked if you'd stop doing that.

235
00:10:44,877 --> 00:10:47,135
That's exactly what's been
wrong with you lately.

236
00:10:47,136 --> 00:10:49,196
Since when do you
side with management?

237
00:10:50,291 --> 00:10:52,805
Ooh, best-case scenario:

238
00:10:52,806 --> 00:10:54,052
old lady.

239
00:10:55,899 --> 00:10:58,479
What's with you?
That is awesome!

240
00:10:58,480 --> 00:11:00,210
How about a little life?

241
00:11:00,211 --> 00:11:02,302
So what, you're just going to
mope around like that guy in...

242
00:11:02,303 --> 00:11:03,962
what's that book where
the guy's mom dies...

243
00:11:03,963 --> 00:11:05,676
and he comes back to Jersey?

244
00:11:05,709 --> 00:11:07,651
He's got that motorcycle sidecar.

245
00:11:07,652 --> 00:11:09,495
Garden State was never a book.

246
00:11:09,496 --> 00:11:11,962
It wasn't? Oops.

247
00:11:11,963 --> 00:11:13,763
So much for that paper.

248
00:11:13,764 --> 00:11:15,885
But if this were a book...

249
00:11:15,886 --> 00:11:18,128
the theme of my essay would be...

250
00:11:18,129 --> 00:11:20,204
the symbolism of how your character...

251
00:11:20,205 --> 00:11:22,677
had his man parts ripped off by
the Veronica Mars character.

252
00:11:22,678 --> 00:11:24,418
My man parts are intact.

253
00:11:24,419 --> 00:11:25,516
Show me.

254
00:11:25,517 --> 00:11:28,021
Well, you'll have to take my word for it.

255
00:11:28,022 --> 00:11:29,579
I mean, symbolically.

256
00:11:29,580 --> 00:11:32,199
We're young, single men
in our sexual prime...

